---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — Artem Belozertsev"
  description="[PLACEHOLDER] Background, interests, and contact."
>
  <h1
    class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-hero font-semibold text-[#e8e8f0] mb-12"
  >
    About
  </h1>

  <div class="space-y-16">
    <section aria-labelledby="about-intro-heading">
      <h2
        id="about-intro-heading"
        class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl text-[#e8e8f0] mb-6"
      >
        Intro
      </h2>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-14 items-start"
      >
        <div class="floating-portrait-outer shrink-0 w-[300px] h-[360px]">
          <div data-floating-portrait class="w-full h-full">
            <div
              class="floating-portrait-frame w-full h-full rounded-xl border border-[rgba(0,240,255,0.15)] bg-[#1a1a24] shadow-glow-cyan overflow-hidden"
            >
              <img
                src="/profile_image.jpg"
                width="300"
                height="360"
                loading="lazy"
                alt="Portrait of Artem Belozertsev"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover object-[50%_35%] opacity-90"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#7a7a9a] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          I'm Artem, a first-year BSc Finance with Mathematics student at the University of Exeter. 
          Originally from Russia, I'm passionate about quantitative finance, financial markets, and the intersection of data science with trading. 
          Outside academics i just create content online, and stay active through basketball, fitness, and running.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="about-background-heading">
      <h2
        id="about-background-heading"
        class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl text-[#e8e8f0] mb-6"
      >
        Background
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[#7a7a9a] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        I am Artem Belozertsev, a Finance with Mathematics student at the University of Exeter, originally from Russia. My journey into finance began long before university — driven by a genuine fascination with how markets work, how numbers tell stories, and how data can predict the future. Growing up with an analytical mindset and a curiosity for global economics, I knew early on that I wanted to build a career at the cutting edge of finance and technology.
After completing my International Foundation Programme at Exeter, I transitioned into my BSc Finance with Mathematics degree — a programme that perfectly bridges my two core interests: the rigour of pure mathematics and the dynamic complexity of financial markets. Modules in calculus, statistics, and financial theory have given me a strong academic foundation, while my own self-directed learning in Python, data analysis, and quantitative methods keeps me pushing further than the curriculum alone.
Beyond the lecture hall, I've always been entrepreneurially minded. I founded and ran a dropshipping business in the UK market, sourcing and selling retro MP3 players and aesthetic Japanese electronics — managing everything from product selection and supplier relationships to content creation, social media marketing, and customer experience. It taught me how to think commercially, move fast, and solve real-world problems with limited resources.
My long-term ambition is to break into quantitative finance or fintech — whether that's in trading, financial modelling, or building data-driven tools that reshape how we interact with markets. I'm drawn to roles where mathematics, programming, and market intuition converge, and I'm actively building the skills to get there: deepening my Python, exploring machine learning applications in finance, and considering professional qualifications like the CQF further down the line.
Outside of work and study, I stay grounded through basketball, gym sessions, and running — sport has always been part of how I focus and recharge. I'm also a content creator at heart, with a passion for video production and storytelling that feeds directly into how I communicate ideas professionally. When I'm not training or studying, you'll likely find me deep in an anime series or researching the next market trend.
I'm currently based between Colchester and Exeter, open to internships, collaborations, and conversations about quantitative finance, fintech, and ambitious projects.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="about-skills-heading">
      <h2
        id="about-skills-heading"
        class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl text-[#e8e8f0] mb-6"
      >
        Interests &amp; Skills
      </h2>
      <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 max-w-3xl" role="list">
        {
          [
            "Quantitative Finance",
            "Python",
            "Mathematics and Statistics",
            "Financial Analysis & Modelling",
            "Trading",
            "Entrepreneurship",
            "Data Science",
            "Excel / Google Sheets",
            "Design + 3D modelling"
          ].map((label) => (
            <li>
              <span
                class="inline-flex items-center min-h-[44px] px-4 rounded-lg border border-[rgba(0,240,255,0.2)] bg-[#0f0f1a] text-sm text-[#e8e8f0] shadow-glow-cyan transition-interactive hover:border-[rgba(0,240,255,0.35)]"
              >
                {label}
              </span>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="about-reading-heading">
      <h2
        id="about-reading-heading"
        class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl text-[#e8e8f0] mb-6"
      >
        Currently Reading / Learning
      </h2>
      <ul
        class="list-disc list-inside text-[#7a7a9a] space-y-3 max-w-2xl marker:text-[#00f0ff]"
        role="list"
      >
        <li>[AAAA] Book, course, or paper title one</li>
        <li>[bbbb] Book, course, or paper title two</li>
        <li>[bbbb] Book, course, or paper title three</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="about-contact-heading">
      <h2
        id="about-contact-heading"
        class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl text-[#e8e8f0] mb-6"
      >
        Get In Touch
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[#7a7a9a] mb-4 max-w-2xl">
        [PLACEHOLDER] Prefer email or LinkedIn — links below are placeholders.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a
          href="#"
          class="inline-flex items-center min-h-[44px] text-[#00f0ff] font-medium transition-interactive hover:text-[#7afcff]"
          >Email (placeholder)</a
        >
        <a
          href="#"
          class="inline-flex items-center min-h-[44px] text-[#00f0ff] font-medium transition-interactive hover:text-[#7afcff]"
          >LinkedIn (placeholder)</a
        >
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
